HEADWORD: Viroled
<hw>Vi*roled"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Her.)</fld>
<def>Furnished with a virole or viroles; -- said of a horn or a bugle
when the rings are of different tincture from the rest of the
horn.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

